
READ ME FIRST!!!
1. identify the number of adverts on the first page
2. Know where the stopped before and after the advert. or know many advert that has rating.
3. It is better to sort by rating and use the url to scrape the web for the required info.


http://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms=coffee&geo_location_terms=Los+Angeles%2C+CA
http://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms=coffee&geo_location_terms=Los%20Angeles%2C%20CA&page=2

http://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms=coffee&geo_location_terms=Los%20Angeles%2C%20CA


Sort by Rating:

http://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms=coffee&geo_location_terms=Los%20Angeles%2C%20CA&s=average_rating&page=10

http://www.yellowpages.com/search?search_terms=coffee&geo_location_terms=Los%20Angeles%2C%20CA&s=average_rating&page=1
